 Children watch a movie with their parents at the Children's Cinematheque in central Israeli city of Holon, on Nov. 30, 2021. The Children's Cinematheque, the first cinema in Israel especially for children, was launched last week by the Holon Mediatheque and the Holon Municipality. The new Cinematheque which aims to bring children closer to the art of cinema, offers a unique film viewing experience for children and the whole family. (Photo by Gil Cohen Magen/Xinhua)  Children watch a movie with their parents at the Children's Cinematheque in central Israeli city of Holon, on Nov. 30, 2021. The Children's Cinematheque, the first cinema in Israel especially for children, was launched last week by the Holon Mediatheque and the Holon Municipality. The new Cinematheque which aims to bring children closer to the art of cinema, offers a unique film viewing experience for children and the whole family. (Photo by Gil Cohen Magen/Xinhua)  A staff member prepares for a movie at the Children's Cinematheque in central Israeli city of Holon, on Nov. 30, 2021. The Children's Cinematheque, the first cinema in Israel especially for children, was launched last week by the Holon Mediatheque and the Holon Municipality. The new Cinematheque which aims to bring children closer to the art of cinema, offers a unique film viewing experience for children and the whole family. (Photo by Gil Cohen Magen/Xinhua)